  "market_context": "Late August 2023 on the ES daily chart, after a multi-month uptrend from ~4100 to ~4680. The analyst examines recent swing points to determine whether price displaced or failed to displace beyond them, forming the basis for daily bias.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst observed that price failed to displace above a recent swing high (returned into range) and failed to displace below a recent swing low (also returned into range), but then successfully displaced upward out of a higher swing high, indicating bullish daily bias.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify recent swing highs and swing lows on the ES daily chart.",
    "Step 2: Check whether price displaced (closed beyond with aggressive candles) or failed to displace (returned into the range) from each swing point.",
    "Step 3: Note that price failed to displace above one swing high and failed to displace below one swing low, both returning into the range.",
    "Step 4: Observe that price then displaced upward out of a subsequent higher swing high and continued outside the range, confirming bullish daily bias."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Daily bias is derived from displacement behavior at key swing points: failure to displace suggests range-bound or reversal potential, while successful displacement confirms directional momentum and sets the intraday bias for trade filtering.",
